         <div type="translation" resp="#jmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p>To Emperor Caesar <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">, chief</supplied> priest <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>, 
               greatest victor in Persia, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> father <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> </p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Third century emperors with this title are Severus Alexander 222-235, Philip in 244, Gallienus 253-268, Vaballathus 270-271, Carus 282-3, Carinus 283-5, Diocletian 284-305. 
               From the style of the lettering the inscription can hardly be later. </p>
         </div>
